tip.text: Cool space and great lunch spot to have amazing tofu squashadillas.
Express veggie tacos for lunch and micheladas. Delish.
Finally a cake selection that differs a bit from the usual stuff: pear and chocolate cake and Nutella and mascarpone cheesecake!
Great smiles behind the counter and a remarkable peanut butter brownie.
Everything was lovely, especially the pulpo and tuna tataki. I am very particular about the way I like tortilla and I found this one a bit bland. Overall I would recommend this place.
Fantastic veggie food and hearty portions in a chilled environment. Baby friendly too.
New favourite Indian restaurant for me - liked it even better than Dishoom. Who knew broccoli could be so tasty??
Come to eat flowers for brunch on a Saturday. Beautiful flavours enhanced by a complimentary glass of cava.
Such great place to hang out. The food is nice and there's a farmers market every Saturday.
In love with the food, unimpressed by (most of) the staff. I will come back for more of that amazing brunch, though.
Chocolate Guinness cake: my new absolute favourite in the world!
A bit of a let-down: the aubergines of my smoked aubergine rice bowl didn't taste smoky but just bland.
Really good vibe in here - the staff is efficient and fun. Loved the ginger loaf, it's so moist.
Great addition to Brick Lane. The space is not as bright as the Goodge Street one and they had scones but no clotted cream, so there's still some room for improvement.
This place never disappoints! You can't go wrong with anything.
Fresh ingredients cooked in a creative way in a chilled and shabby chic atmosphere. Lovely.
So refreshing to find a different brunch menu at last! Surprising flavours and such orange egg yolks. The coffees are prepared with lots of love by the experts of Black Box Coffee.
Bright and stylish space, very popular for brunch. To my dismay, I found my eggs on toast a bit greasy and the halloumi was overcooked.

Not easy to come across it unless you are looking for it, which makes it more especial. There are 2 very different spaces, one more casual and crowded, and the bar opposite, better suited for meetings
I eat loads of cake and have tried many different places around, but there's something far superior about The Coffice cakes. Everything tastes homemade, natural and uncomplicated.

formattedAddress: The Brew Eagle House, 163 City Road, London, EC1V 1NR (163 City Road)
location.address: The Brew Eagle House, 163 City Road, London, EC1V 1NR

tip.text: These guys have the recipe for a perfect hangover cure. Everything is hearty, tasty and the portions are BIG.
Lovely tea and healthy sweet balls.
A real gem for foodies in Wendover. We stocked up on cheese, candy and local IPAs.
Cute little café with comfy sofas and loads of natural light. I should have never ordered that hot cross bun, though.

formattedAddress: 108 London Rd, Aston Clinton, Aylesbury, Buckinghamshire
location.address: 108 London Rd, Aston Clinton, Aylesbury, Buckinghamshire

tip.text: Duck filled croissants, decent cake selection and great coffee. The guy behind the counter couldn't be nicer!
Back here, this time for lunch. The views are more spectacular than the food, except for the Marmite semifredo, which is just fantastic.

formattedAddress: Level 31 The Shard (31 St Thomas St)

tip.text: An oasis in the area. If you are feeling a bit adventurous, try the baked eggs: hearty and spicy. Well deserved high rating!
Cosy country pub, attentive staff and delicious food which comes in hearty portions. This place is quite a find.
Such lovely cakes and cute space. The hummingbird is seriously good.
I recommend the brownie to those in need of a chocolate overdose. For a spongy experience, the chocolate and coconut cake is so lovely and moist.
The almond and pistachio cronut is so so good. And the lady behind the counter was really cheerful, so everything was spot on.
A truly incredible culinary experience. Every dish was an explosion of flavours. My favourite? The gazpacho.
There's beauty in every corner of this place. The staff is attentive and lovely and the wild mushrooms on ricotta toast is just delicious. New favourite brunch place in East London.
Hearty but digestion friendly bowls, full of flavour and goodness. Loved it!
When coming for lunch, choose a table under the skylight. The space is beautifully decorated and the food was really tasty. Works well for a business lunch too.
Stylish space, comfortable, not crowded and spacious. It is overall a great experience, however for £15 a ticket I expect not to have to clean leftover popcorn from my seat.
Everything was delicious, specially the burnt courgette tzatziki, the octo-hummous and the josperised aubergine. The only downside is that it gets a bit smoky inside due to the open kitchen.
Interesting space including a Korean restaurant, a café and a barber. Loved the vibe, so will be coming back to try their Korean recipes.
Cute shop and café. I come here for their cacti and succulents.
I love this place. So many times I've been here to only recently try the desserts: they are so good I will make sure in the future to always leave space for them. Black sesame crème brûlée!
One of the best Chinese meals I've had in a while. Dim sum staples, Sichuan dishes and a bunch of classic mains to choose from. The bean curd stuffed aubergines are a new favorite for me.
Really chilled space where you can sit back, relax and enjoy those delicious chocolate pastries

There is nothing for you here, vegetarians. If you eat fish, they use some for the broth, but all dishes contain meat, so they just remove it, don't replace it with anything and you still pay the same
Amazing fried rosquetes. So tender and covered in sugar! They also have fancy pretty cakes.
Local dishes with a twist. Everything was delicious but the portions were gigantic! First time in my life I walk away from a restaurant carrying half the food with me. Too good to waste it!
Fantastic place. The gardens, the traditional architecture, the view and of course the service and the restaurant: everything is excellent. The orange, figs and cod salad is beyond delicious.

formattedAddress: 38800 San Sebastián de la Gomera Canarias

tip.text: Traditional biscuits and rosquetes, but also essentials such as cheese, salchichón, bread... Great service and food.
The bread is one of the best we found on the island, so we kind of ignored the fact that it's much more expensive than average.
Such a gem: the staff couldn't be friendlier and the food was simply fantastic. The tuna croquetas are incredibly tasty, their grandma's recipe.
Food rarely gets as homemade as this in a restaurant. Fresh fish and lovely service. Do not miss the local dessert: yogur con miel de palma y plátano
Cool place but disappointing experience: we were kicked out of our table before we managed to finish our teas for a reservation we weren't made aware of. How rude.
Come here for authentic blood dripping stakes: Basque chuletones. I had cod though and it was great, but I found the torrija for dessert disappointing, far from the real thing. Great place overall.
The lunch set menu on the weekend is not only very tasty, but also great value. The risotto was delicious.
Delicious and wallet friendly Indian street food. The Bollywood tunes will have you bouncing on your chair.
Nice coffee and sandwiches. I wish there were more places like this in Whitechapel.
Gone are the days where meat was the only option. Check out the vegetarian and pescatarian menus and have the crispy prawn kale as a starter. The ambiance is really cool here.
The pho is nice, but not nice enough to put up with having all of yourself smelling of Vietnamese restaurant for the rest of the day. Get a takeaway.
Absolutely a fan of their crodoughs. How can they be SO GOOD? The guys are lovely as well!
Coffee is roasted in this beautiful and modern space. The only downside is sitting by the kitchen: you will end up smelling of whatever they are cooking.
The Swedes know their cinnamon buns and these ones are just insanely good, especially when warm.
I found the natto set menu a bit bland, but the matcha cheesecake is worth to live for.
Seafood and fried aubergines. It gets busy, so you might as well book.
We tried a lot of things and everything was beyond delicious, from the seafood to the meats. Take a walk and check the dessert shelve - homemade natillas are a favourite.
Fancy daily menu. Big portions, great quality and a very good service.
Tapas with a Latin American twist. The fruit salad is a colourful starter, not a dessert as one would think.
Traditional bar. The chiporones are to die for.
Unfortunately the baked goods are a bit dry. The staff is nice and helpful, so they will warm up the scones for you and that will make wonders. No clotted cream, though.
The Christmas set dinner was incredibly disappointing. None of the starters were suitable for pregnancy, so they gave me instead an instant soup with stale bread. I won't be coming back. Ever.
Beers, burgers and fancy lemonade for those on the wagon.
There are less options now on the set menu, however everything was delicious as usual and the service was as great as ever.
Ceviche is the best option for starter. Then have the black cod with lobster mash, it's so so good. Service was lovely but incredibly slow, but they made up for it with free deserts.
Cosy and old fashioned hotel in Mitte. Comfortable beds and nice German breakfast.
Veggie alert! All soups are made with some sort of meat. Check out the board for the daily specials, there's always something vegetarian and delicious.
Popular spot for breakfast. I get the hype, but to me there was an excessive use of seasoning. Also the müsli was too sweet...
Everything was excellent: the views, the atmosphere, the staff and of course the food. Finish your meal with the crème brûlée.
My favourite was the Chinese broccoli signature dish. This place is challenging if you don't eat meat (I eat fish), but I had pork by mistake in their prawn wanton dumpling soup. Service is messy.
Not bad. The Christmas set dinner is hearty and less fancy than the à la carte one, but everything was quite tasty. Lovely cocktails.
There is a before and after when you have had an almond croissant from this place: my new found love.
I had the halloumi souvlaki as a takeaway for lunch, but felt similar to a 3am kebab. The halloumi is delicious, but the chips inside made it feel like a brick in my tummy.

formattedAddress: Boxpark Shoreditch, Unit 54, 2-10 Bethnal Green Road
location.address: Boxpark Shoreditch, Unit 54, 2-10 Bethnal Green Road

tip.text: Even if this place is famous for its mixed grill, there is hope for vegetarians: 6/7 veggie dishes on the menu.
Quirky, kitsch and... expensive! £7.50 for a no frills twinning tea and a hot chocolate. The toilet smelt anything but clean and there's nothing to dry your hands there. Quite disappointing.
Three veggie options! THREE! That is a luxury for a ramen place. My new fave is Tantamen 3: so creamy and spicy.
Perfect pit stop to regain energy during a hike. It's cozy, friendly, a few centuries old and a great place for both bar food or a fancy meal. Absolutely loved it.
We had a bumpy start when they announced on a Saturday at lunch time that they only had enough dough to make ONE pizza. Luckily I got it and it was delicious, so that saved the day.
Unpretentious Turkish restaurant: great service, huge portions and affordable prices.

Fantastic lemonade, coffee and of course, the cakes. We had carrot and chestnut, which were to die for. Our waiter was a lovely and interesting man, I wanted to hug him! Can't praise this place enough
Veggie does not always mean healthy, especially if you have the tacos. However everything was really tasty and the venue is a cozy and interesting space.
Modern rustic space, friendly service and delicious comfort food. Veggie options and menu in English. I loved this place.
Pretty average comfort food. However, the staff was wonderful and helped us as much as they could to translate the menu.
Small and super busy cake shop. It's really popular for a reason, the cakes are delicious and they also serve ice cream and good coffee to go.
The best meal I've had in a long time. Both the pork cheeks and the rainbow trout were out of this world. Highly recommended.
Mostly convenient when you land or depart from Terminal 3, although there is a free shuttle.. The staff is lovely and somewhat quirky, the breakfast buffet combines local and international foods.
Why is it so difficult to find a place that can be bothered to serve veggie gravy? We also deserve a juicy roast on a Sunday. The cheerfulness of the stuff almost made up for this.
The sweet choice is broad and super cool, but serving potato soup is just poor. Any vegetable is more exciting than a potato, and trust me, that soup didn't seem to contain anything else.
Looks are deceiving: bland food, poor service, disappointing experience.
Nice pub by the canal. Avoid the yellowfin tuna, it's overcooked. The burgers are great though, especially the veggie one.
Disappointed to find out that the avocado vegan cake is moist on the top but super dry at the bottom. Really busy as well - it's pretty much a co-working space.

formattedAddress: 7 Upper St Martin's Ln (Tower St and Monmouth St)

tip.text: I doubted the authenticity of this place by it's modern, high-street look, but I have to admit this udon is really really tasty. Suitable for veggies, pescatarians and carnivores alike.
Food was excellent, really tasty (be advised dishes are oily). Galicia octopus with ajoblanco is sublime. Lovely decor and great service.
I am not particularly crazy about their sandwiches, but I could kill for their pear galette. Beyond delicious.
Beautiful food in a tastefully decorated dinning room. Great for client entertainment, though the service is a bit slow. Plum + Spilt Milk dessert is just wonderful.

formattedAddress: Great Northern Hotel (King’s Cross St Pancras Station)

tip.text: Kaya toast is to die for. If you feel adventurous, have the steamed toast with peanut butter!

venue.name: Ya Kun Kaya Toast 亞坤

tip.text: Avoid the hoards and you will save an hour of your life waiting to be served. Come before and after. Fresh, delicious fish and sides. Friendly prices.
Pretty decent ice-cream and good flavour selection, including local and classic flavours. I had whisky cream and coconut pandan.
Candlelit BBQ fish dinner is fantastic here. So is the service and the Chill Out Dream dessert.
It took a while to get our food, as they make it from scratch. Gado gado was really good and such gigantic portion I struggled to finish it! Very healthy.
Best cakes we had on the island, specially the vegan friendly carrot cake. Super moist!
No frills, authentic Indonesian food. It was delicious and ridiculously cheap. Don't expect big portions for those prices, though!
Had The Delicious, which is super super sweet, and the mini muffins, that are very pretty but not amazing. Cheerful staff and cute sitting area.
Fabulous healthy food in a stylish café. Bowls are beautiful and the quinoa salad a big pot of goodness.
We only had dinner here to achieve the minimum spend required for their movie night. My Thai soup was good, but nasi campur was mediocre and small in size. Perhaps is best to do drinks and movie.
This place is fabulous. Fish satay is really tasty and if you want to experiment with a local dessert, dadar gulung is a must. Book to jump the queue!
Extensive veggie menu. My gluten free chocolate cake was okay, but definitely small. The views are lovely though.
After having breakfast, lunch and dinner here, I suggest to stick to brekkie. The bread is organic and if you are up for something different, go for the black rice pudding with coconut cream.
The seafood sate was nice, especially the homemade peanut sauce and sambals. However the noodles taste really MSG-artificial. Avoid. All in all, I found everything oily and overpriced.
Sit in one the bamboo booths and enjoy a fantastic meal and great service. Fusion food, French-Indonesian. Have ice cream, it's so good!
Everything is cooked from scratch for you, so sit back and enjoy the view. The wait is more than worth it because every dish was spectacular. Try the steamed balinese pumpkin cake!
When you're destroyed after hiking, anything tastes good. But these guys do really great food with a lovely view.
The type of laid back coffee where you could chill for hours, surfing the Internet, sipping "I am Tarzan" coconut water and having healthy and beautiful dishes.

Beautiful food for a good cause. You will contribute to building a hospital and provide health care for those in need. To top it off, everything we had was delicious, especially the papaya/prawn salad
Fresh, clean, organic food with a view. Loved it!
All the ingredients are sourced locally and they have mindfully tagged the ice creams so you know if there's dairy, gluten, etc. in them. The raw chocolate is the best thing ever!!
Definitely a trendy spot. We went for the specials, which were good, but the portions are a bit small.
Had a gigantic Gorilla Salad and loved it. They also have kombucha!
Micro-brewary with loads of outdoor space in Dalston
Authentic micheladas in East London.
Dover sole. Off the bone. Looks boring but it is insanely good.
Today I had scallops and they melted in my mouth.
Tons of butter and cream and generous portions designed for a big belly.
Cosy place, yummy cocktails and great service. Try their Hugo or Lily cocktails - they're not on the menu though!
Bright space, lovely food and if you are not a coffee drinker, they've got nice loose teas and matcha lattes.
Extensive drinks menu to relax and work from the lobby in the most sophisticated manner.
If you are not up for a blood dripping piece of meat, the tuna steak is the best option by far. Yum!
Sweet and savoury heaven.
Try their vegan cakes. Out of this world!!
Initially disappointed about the lack of lunch menu, as advertised on their website, we found the brunch alternative really tasty. Gazpacho is not the real thing, but pretty good nonetheless.
El menú del día está bien, pero lo de que no hubiera papel en el baño me dejó muerta.
A real Turkish eatery: nothing fancy or hipster-like here, but the service was great and the food excellent and in huge amounts!
Beautiful and divine éclair.
Absolutely delightful. Scallop poke and monkfish! Perfect place for a business meal or a romantic date.
Treat yourself to a lobster brioche roll, cocktails and oysters.
Dim sum that melts in your mouth, cocktails and a stylish and decadent environment.

formattedAddress: 15-16 Gerrard St (btwn Wardour St & Gerrard Pl)

tip.text: This place never disappoints. Wonderful 4 course menu, really creative in a bright and stylish space.
Second time here. I take back my previous tip - this time the service was excellent and the turbot was light and delightful.
Freshest pasta in a minimal, stylish and relaxing environment. Could eat here every day!
Chill and drink yummy juice at the courtyard.
Rumours have it the chef is from Belgium, but no one will notice because this place is designed for foreigners like us. Lovely food, attention and sunsets though.
What a delightful experience. Even the toilets are so pretty you wouldn't mind getting your meal served there.
Very authentic: mouthwatering dishes, blunt staff.
Great setting, decor, loads of natural light and those amazing eggs (pictured).
People come from all over the world just to have a piece of their signature chocolate and Guinness cake. Not surprised, it's the BEST THING EVA!
Views, cheesy music, natural light and slightly chewy cinnamon rolls.
A creative and different brunch. Delicious. Mimosas could be improved with real orange juice though.
If you are starving after all that museum wandering, have a scone here. Ignore the teas, poor selection.
Truffle edamame? Calpico? Veggie ramen? Bring them all on! Really impressed, this ramen is out of this world.
Get a table at the jungle room for a decadent Sunday branch. I had eggs on sourdough even if that wasn't on the menu. And mimosas, plenty of mimosas.
The lunch menu is incredibly great value. The food, presentation and service are sublime. Original menu and ample selection of yummy dishes.
Dessert orgy to top up the most wonderful sushi feast.
Beautiful place, unimpressed by the food.
Dark chocolate ice cream?? How marvelous!
Everything tastes good and the place is quite cute - it's just a bit westernised.
The menu changes daily and it's always amazing. Creative and generous in size, this is quite an upgrade compared to the other restaurants on the beach.
Awesome place to chill during the day and have a healthy lunch. Just make sure you order before you are starving, it takes a while to get your food.
Great sunbeds, juices and fruit platters. Don't bother with the food though - tiny portions and virtually no ingredients in them. E.g. veggie rice: a lot of rice with just a bit of carrot.
Tiny portions when it comes to mains, although desserts are a bit more decent in size... Everything tasty, though.
An upmarket alternative to more modest accommodation around. Westernised, though.
The freshest ingredients prepared right next to you. The string hoppers were delish and the cook kept refilling the bowls. One of the best meals we have had in Sri Lanka.
Classic place for backpackers. Food caters for all tastes and it's alright. Our waiter was the highlight, a really nice guy!
Watalappam, some sort of coconut custard. It's crazy sweet, soooooo yummy!
Loved the coconut prawns! Cute colonial building.
More soya stuff that you've probably ever seen! All snacks are veggie or vegan, but the absolute highlight are the ice creams.
Pick one of this babies and get it cooked the way you love. Top it up with the pumpkin pudding for desert. Tea and chocolates at the end were on the house.
My absolute new favourite decadent cocktail den in Brick Lane. Dimly lit, not too crowded and great choice of music and staff - we had a laugh!!
Great selection of Spanish and Portuguese staples. The wine choice feels a bit limited, but all the food was excellent. Take my advice, I was born in the Iberian Peninsula.

Most amazing and creative chocolates!! These guys starting up selling just two types of truffles and now they are running this emporium. The only thing I can't condone is the horrible music they play.
Great value express lunch menu: big portions, starter and main, plus the possibility to get a tofu version of all the main dishes.
Loved listening to classical music in the loo. Now, roast wise, it is definitely more worth it if you are carnivorous: the veggie stuff is not impressive and it's too expensive for what you get.
Inexpensive and quite decent afternoon tea. Make sure you sit outside or by the windows in the inclement weather - the space at the back is somewhat grim.
I loved the halibut, whereas the risotto lobster and the mozzarella salad were a bit bland. Also, the staff was nice, but not genuinely nice.
Finally a local coffee place in the area that is opened until 8pm. Great sweet and savory selection and comfy and beautiful space.
Dodgy looking on the outside, cosy and hip inside. If like me, you don't find the perfect cocktail, just ask them to concoct something specially tailored for you.
Perfectly cooked eggs, really bright yolks so they must be organic. Just make sure you find a spot in the sun, because the wait to get the food is long. That is just not cool on a hungover Sunday.
Modern Turkish cuisine. Everything was tasty and beautifully presented, however it didn't blow my mind. It's okay, just not amazing.
Don't even dream of ordering Gordon's here. Great gin selection, needless to say it gets even better when it comes to wine. Perfect location and really cosy inside.
A paradise for matcha lovers. Wonderful explosion of green flavours with a kick. Pure synesthesia.
Everything was absolutely amazing, specially the tinned cod and the daily specials. All dishes are really oily: our hands were greasy in spite of using cutlery in a very civilised manner.
Great lunch deal. Spicing it up with margaritas is my recommendation.
Definitely hip, so I get the hype, but I would say the food is overrated and probably overpriced. Except the sweet potato fries. Oh, those are so yummy!!
Tiny café with a strong character. They do matcha latte and the vegan slices are simply divine.
Friendly pub. Check out the daily specials for a slightly more interesting choice.
Wow. Ramen here is out of this world. Best veggie one I've probably ever had. Worth the queue.
Relax upstairs with some chocolate and pistachio marble cake - the avocado and chocolate was nowhere to be seen, which broke my heart  a bit.
Eating banaba bread and sipping Moroccan whisky. Sheer bliss.
It feels this place is a bit of a Hakkasan wannabe. In any case, the black cod was absolutely delicious, one of those that melt in your mouth.

formattedAddress: 38-40 James St (par. w/ St Christopher's Place)

tip.text: A chunk of East London in Holborn. Brekkie here is hearty and delish!
What a great addition to the Wapping dining scene. The Quinta da Portela Albergue do Bonjardim, from Portugal, was my absolute favourite red.
Delightful place, stunning decor with a soundtrack from the 20's. The food was absolutely lovely, specially the cod and the chocolate panna cotta (pictured).
Don't be fooled by the good looks of their cakes:they are dry and massively disappointing.
My new favourite in the Pho Mile. Not an easy decision as the competition around is really good, however the monkfish with dill won my tummy and my heart. Delicious. And really cheap!
There's a special light in other. Wonderful place to hang out and learn more about the evolution of the British household. Free entry.
